# Monorepo Architecture

## Layout

```
apps/
  devinity-api/     # NestJS API (DVN)
  devinity-web/     # Next.js frontend (DVN)
  take-and-do/      # Next.js full-stack app (TAD)
  personal-website/ # Next.js site (PRT)
packages/
  @repo/api         # Shared models, DTOs, HTTP helpers
  @repo/ui          # Shared React components
  @repo/shared      # Shared TS utilities
  @repo/eslint-config
  @repo/typescript-config
  @repo/vitest-config
```

## Import boundaries

- Apps **must not** import source from other apps (`apps/foo` → `apps/bar` is forbidden).
- Shared code goes through workspace packages: `@repo/api`, `@repo/ui`, `@repo/shared`, etc.
- Use package **exports** — do not reach into another package's `src/` via relative paths from apps.
- Root `package.json` scripts orchestrate builds; prefer root commands over per-app `pnpm build` when matching CI.

## Turborepo pipeline

From `turbo.json`:

- `build` → `dependsOn: ["^build"]` — upstream packages build first.
- `dev` → `dependsOn: ["^build"]`, `cache: false`, `persistent: true`.
- `lint`, `codeCheck`, `test`, `test:e2e` → `dependsOn: ["^<task>"]` — run upstream first.
- `prod` → `dependsOn: ["build"]`.

When adding a new package or app task, register it in `turbo.json` and `pnpm-workspace.yaml`.

## Dev entrypoints (root scripts)

- `pnpm dev:devinity` — devinity-api + devinity-web + @repo/api + @repo/ui
- `pnpm dev:take-and-do` — take-and-do + @repo/ui + @repo/api + @repo/shared
- `pnpm dev:personal-website` — personal-website + @repo/ui

## Scope mapping (git / releases)

| SCOPE | App / area |
|-------|------------|
| `GEN` | Repo-wide / tooling |
| `TAD` | take-and-do |
| `DVN` | devinity-api + devinity-web |
| `PRT` | personal-website |
